com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.jsombridge
Class AST2JSOM.AST2JSOMUnmarshaller

java.lang.Object
  com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.antlrbridge.JSOParser
      com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.jsombridge.AST2JSOM.AST2JSOMUnmarshaller
Direct Known Subclasses:
JSourceUnmarshallerBase
Enclosing class:
AST2JSOM
protected static class AST2JSOM.AST2JSOMUnmarshaller
extends com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.antlrbridge.JSOParser

The purpose of this class is to parse Java sources and transform the parser results into appropriate AST2JSOM objects.

This class is only visible to sub-types of the AST2JSOM type. It's unmarshaller methods return AST2JSOM type objects. Unmarshaller methods within classes derived from this class should only return JSOM types without the visibility of all the AST2 stuff. __TEST__ Most unmarshalble code fragments still untested for unmarshalling failure.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

unmarshalAST2JavaSource

public com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.jsombridge.ast2api.AST2JavaSource unmarshalAST2JavaSource(java.io.File pJavaSource,
                                                                                                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                                                                                                 throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals a complete Java source file.

Parameters:
pJavaSource - The Java source that should get unmarshalled.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err. Otherwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type ASTJavaSource. If marshalling the file has been failed but no exception has been thrown null will be returned and it's very likely that there's at least one message within the message list passed to this method (if a list has been passed at all, of course).
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the Java file failed.

unmarshalAST2Expression

public com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.unmarshaller.jsombridge.ast2api.expression.AST2Expression unmarshalAST2Expression(java.lang.String pExpression,
                                                                                                                   java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                                                                                                            throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals any kind of expressions stated by a string.

Important note: The given string must represent a complete expression in a semantical point of view, i.e. an assignment statement, a 'new' expression, a method call and so on. Unmarshalling of a fraction of a complete expression may succeed but this is not guaranteed. For instance, unmarshalling just a primary expression representing an array type declaration (something like anyType[]) will always fail.

Parameters:
pExpression - The expression that should get unmarshalled.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err. Otherwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type AST2Expression.
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the code fragment failed.

                                                                                                                                    java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                                                                                                                             throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals an expression statement stated by a string.

An expression statement is a statement that could also be an expression anywhere else. This could be an assignment expression or a method call, for instance.

Parameters:

pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err. Otherwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type AST2ExpressionStatement. If marshalling the code fragment has been failed but no exception has been thrown null will be returned and it's very likely that there's at least one message within the message list passed to this method (if a list has been passed at all, of course).
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the code fragment failed.

pTryStatement - The try statement that should get unmarshalled. Note that the stated string must contain the complete statement including a catch clause and/or a finally clause and including the statement blocks following the the try/catch/finally keywords.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err. Otherwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type AST2TryStatement. If marshalling the code fragment has been failed but no exception has been thrown null will be returned and it's very likely that there's at least one message within the message list passed to this method (if a list has been passed at all, of course).
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the code fragment failed.
